statements: SELECT * FROM ab_testing_ui_designs;
SELECT experiment_id, design_variant FROM ab_testing_ui_designs WHERE user_id = 100;
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM ab_testing_ui_designs ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;
SELECT design_variant, AVG(engagement_score) AS avg_engagement FROM ab_testing_ui_designs GROUP BY design_variant;
SELECT * FROM ab_testing_ui_designs WHERE experiment_id IN (1, 3, 5);
SELECT * FROM ab_testing_ui_designs WHERE design_variant = 'Variant A';
SELECT user_id, design_variant FROM ab_testing_ui_designs ORDER BY user_id DESC;
SELECT AVG(engagement_score) AS avg_score, COUNT(*) AS num_experiments FROM ab_testing_ui_designs;
SELECT DISTINCT user_id, design_variant FROM ab_testing_ui_designs WHERE engagement_score > 0.5 ORDER BY user_id, design_variant;
SELECT * FROM ab_testing_ui_designs WHERE experiment_id IN (1, 3, 5) ORDER BY user_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM user_interface_designs;
SELECT design_name, version FROM user_interface_designs WHERE engagement_score > 8;
SELECT design_name, engagement_score FROM user_interface_designs WHERE version = 'v2';
SELECT * FROM ab_test_results ORDER BY conversion_rate DESC;
SELECT test_id, test_date FROM ab_test_results WHERE user_id = 123;
SELECT * FROM user_interface_designs WHERE version = 'v1.0';
SELECT design_name, engagement_score FROM user_interface_designs ORDER BY engagement_score DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT user_id, test_date, conversion_rate FROM ab_test_results WHERE test_id = 101 ORDER BY test_date DESC;
SELECT design_id, COUNT(test_id) AS total_tests, AVG(conversion_rate) AS avg_conversion_rate FROM ab_test_results GROUP BY design_id HAVING avg_conversion_rate > 0.5;
SELECT design_name, version, engagement_score FROM user_interface_designs WHERE engagement_score > 8.0 AND version LIKE 'v%' ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;
SELECT * FROM user_interface_designs;
SELECT * FROM user_data ORDER BY signup_date DESC;
SELECT design_name, engagement_score FROM user_interface_designs WHERE engagement_score > 0.5;
SELECT user_email, signup_date FROM user_data WHERE user_id = 10;
SELECT DISTINCT design_id FROM experiment_results ORDER BY design_id;
SELECT * FROM user_interface_designs ORDER BY design_name DESC, engagement_score ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT user_id, user_email, design_id, signup_date FROM user_data WHERE signup_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT design_name, experiment_id, engagement_score FROM user_interface_designs WHERE engagement_score > 8.5 ORDER BY engagement_score DESC;

SELECT ud.user_email, ui.design_name, er.conversion_rate FROM user_data ud JOIN user_interface_designs ui ON ud.design_id = ui.design_id JOIN experiment_results er ON ud.design_id = er.design_id WHERE er.conversion_rate > 0.5;
SELECT experiment_id, AVG(conversion_rate) AS avg_conversion_rate FROM experiment_results GROUP BY experiment_id HAVING avg_conversion_rate > 0.7 ORDER BY avg_conversion_rate DESC;
SELECT * FROM users ORDER BY username DESC;
SELECT user_id, username, email FROM users WHERE registration_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT design_name, design_description FROM designs WHERE latest_version = true;
SELECT experiment_name, start_date FROM experiments WHERE end_date > '2022-06-30';
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM results WHERE experiment_id = 1;
SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = 'JohnDoe';
SELECT user_id, email FROM users WHERE registration_date > '2021-01-01';
SELECT design_name, design_description FROM designs WHERE latest_version = true;
SELECT experiment_name, start_date, end_date FROM experiments WHERE start_date < '2022-01-01' ORDER BY end_date DESC;
SELECT user_id, engagement_score FROM results WHERE engagement_score > 0.8 ORDER BY user_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM user_accounts WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT username, email FROM user_accounts WHERE account_type = 'admin';
SELECT registration_date FROM user_accounts ORDER BY registration_date DESC;
SELECT interaction_type, interaction_date FROM user_interactions WHERE user_id = 3 ORDER BY interaction_date ASC;
SELECT test_name, start_date, end_date FROM ab_tests WHERE end_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM user_accounts WHERE user_id = 1;
SELECT username, email FROM user_accounts WHERE account_type = 'premium';
SELECT user_id, email, registration_date FROM user_accounts ORDER BY registration_date DESC;
SELECT user_id, count(*) AS interactions_count FROM user_interactions GROUP BY user_id HAVING count(*) > 5;
SELECT test_id, test_name, start_date, end_date FROM ab_tests WHERE end_date >= CURRENT_DATE;
